HEADWORD: Piezometer
<hw>Pi`e*zom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to
press + <ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pi⟦eacute⟧zom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for measuring the
compressibility of liquids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>A gauge connected with a water
main to show the pressure at that point.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

